07 Apr 2012 11:29






1st; I still think that can be rephrased to something better. Your computer is perfectly capable of an internet connection, yet it does not have a T3 NIC. Hence  may be a better phrase.

2nd; OK, point taken.

3rd; 44 megabits? Oh come on, the article was wrtitten 3 years ago. Gigabit ethernet came into being at least 8 years ago.

4th; I object. This thing operates at OSI level 3. The NIC at the computer it is connected to operates at OSI level 3. Files belong to level 7. So, unless some serious SCP magic is happening at the computer, files are not what you should see. Also, in case of Linux-based network equipment you can telnet / ssh to them and change the configuration in-place, via files or commands, but you don't see the files right after you connect your PC to it.

5th; Maybe. The latter makes the whole thing creepier.







